The amplifier has multiple input terminals, one for each component in the DAC's input chain.

The diagram also includes labels that describe the components: "DAC" for the DAC and "OPA303" for the amplifier. Additionally, there are arrows pointing to the respective input terminals on both sides of the circuit, indicating the direction of the audio signal flow within the system.
